The City of Chesterfield will be hosting an Art Exhibit at City Hall from January 15 through March 31 from 8:30 am to 5:00 pm (excluding holidays) and features two-dimensional artwork, including paintings, mixed media and photographs from established regional artists Mark Witzling, Jeane Vogel and sculptures from Paul Bayer. The artist’s full bios are available at chesterfield.mo.us. A guided tour of the Art Exhibit will be offered on Thursday, February 4 at 10:00 am. The tour will cover general overviews to in-depth explorations of the current exhibit and will last between 45 to 60 minutes. To sign up, call Sukanya Mani at 636.812.9523 or email her at smani@chesterfield.mo.us.  
Chesterfield Parks, Recreation & Arts will host an Artist Reception on Friday, February 5 from 5:30 pm to 7:00 pm in the multi-purpose room at City Hall, located at 690 Chesterfield Parkway West, 63017. The reception will offer an intimate setting for art enthusiasts to meet the artists and an opportunity to discuss the inspiration behind their artwork. The event is free to attend and light hors d’oeuvres and cocktails will be served. To RSVP, call Sukanya Mani at 636.812.9523 or email her at smani@chesterfield.mo.us by Friday, January 29 at 5:00 pm.

description.text:

Monday evenings:  January 18th-February 22nd from 6-8 p.m.

description.text:
The Rockhill Women's Bible study is an interdenominational Bible study located in Telford, Pennsylvania.  It is our desire to not just grow in knowledge about how to live better lives, not just to learn more information about God, but rather, through our study of God's Word, we are seeking to grow in KNOWING HIM. You can learn more about us here. 

  
The Rockhhill Women's Bible Study will begin it's 11 week winter/spring session of Bible study on Monday, January 18th. 
We have been working our way through the book of Exodus and will pick up the story of Moses and the people of Israel at the foot of Mt. Sinai in Exodus 19.  
You are invited to join us as we seek to know more intimately God as He reveals Himself through Exodus. Even if you were not a part of Exodus Part I, I would like you to know that you are still welcome to join us. I think you will find that you can jump right in at this point of the study and still benefit, learn and grow. 
You will receive your workbooks on the first night of study. 
If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact me! 
Looking forward to our time together! 
Cherie

I am organizing a fundraiser to support groundbreaking research at Massachusetts General Hospital. His doctor, Dr. Alice Shaw and her team have made incredible breakthroughs in treating the rare cancer my dad has but more research is needed.  
Please help make a difference in our lives and have fun while doing it by joining me at Bounce. The proceeds we generate will go directly to researching treatments for my dad and people like him who are fighting cancer. 
 Please spread the word. All are welcome. Let’s JUMP FOR A CURE! 
Tickets are also available at the door.

description.text:
NSO exists to help and support new students as they transition into the Hope community. A number of activities and seminars are planned to prepare new students for their experience at Hope by exposing them to educational opportunities, helping them develop quality relationships, and encouraging them to access campus resources. Orientation is also the time for new students to celebrate as they take this next step, receive instruction and guidance as they transition into the Hope community, including academic advisement in preparation for registration, and much more. NSO is a part of the department of Student Affairs which strives to provide holistic support for students to grow intellectually, socially, and spiritually. 
Become a part of NSO! This is a great opportunity to get prepared for this new and exciting adventure while getting plugged into the campus community. 
This year our theme is I AM HOPE!  We understand that this is a big transition for students (and their families), and with transition can come lots of changes that may sometimes be difficult.  Through all of this transition, we want students to remain anchored to the Lord and the hope and security He provides. 
The verse for NSO is Isaiah 40:31: but those who hope in the Lord will renew their strength. They will soar on wings like eagles; they will run and not grow weary, they will walk and not be faint. 
We look forward to seeing you on campus! Welcome to Hope and God Bless! 
Gyasmine George-Williams 
Director, Student Involvement & Community Outreach

description.text:
Get a head start 
Become certified 
























  
  
As developers and web-designers, we are expected to know about the best solutions in our area of expertise. We are expected to know the best practice way, as well as the shortcuts that enable us to be more productive and build smarter solutions for our customers - Umbraco master classes are all about giving you those skills - fast. 
Get certified 
Only by attending one of the Umbraco Masterclasses, can you achieve the valuable “Certified Umbraco Developer” status, the certification is available to all masterclass attendees for free. 
  
Level 1 
For web-developers and web-designers 
The level 1 master class is all about enabling you as a developer or designer, to build beautiful managed websites, without knowing anything but html, css and javascript. After 2 focused days, you will be able to turn any static html design into powerful umbraco website, fully managed and with a user-friendly interface for your editors. 

How to create and design your content structure
How you use your own designs with Html and CSS in Umbraco
How to handle media, promotional sliders, and galleries
How users, permissions, and notifications can be used for simple, yet flexible workflows
How multilingual content is handled
How to build your own forms without any code

 Includes the valuable Umbraco Level 1 certification 
  
 Level 2 
For .net and javascript developers and extension builders As a .net developer, you have the tools and skills to hook into any part of Umbraco and tweak it to your liking. The Umbraco APIs gives anyone access to tailor their Umbraco site to their needs, and turn it into a powerful web application. During this 2 day course, you will build a complete intranet application, that through detailed hands-on exercises shows you how powerful the Umbraco api’s really are. 

Project Structure
A deeper look into the Razor syntax
Debugging tips and tools
Caching
Macros
Custom DataTypes and Property Editors
AJAX with WebAPI
Umbraco events
Umbraco service APIs

 Includes the valuable Umbraco Leve 2 certification 
  
Details 
 We provide the coffee, water, and lunches - if you're really good there are some special treats too.  You provide a laptop running Umbraco and WebMatrix (for Level 1) or Visual Studio 2013+ (for Level 2).  We learn together, have some fun, and work hard to make your time worthwhile.

*New* Movement Class in Hillsboro  
Come and participate in a weekly exercise program designed specifically for people living with Parkinson's disease to increase strength, balance, flexibility and overall coordination. This program features many of the principles of the John Argue method (www.JohnArgue.com) with some new twists!  
Cheri Morey is an occupational therapist who has worked in the field for over twenty years.  Ms. Morey has spent most of this time providing skilled therapy services in Rehabilitation facilities and in Home Health.  She has focused her continuing education on gaining specific skills in working with neurological movement disorders and has history with many patients as they work through improving their mobility. 
" My goal is to inspire people to improve their mobility weekly and then independently at home outside of the expense of skilled, outpatient care." - Cheri Morey 
  
Special thanks to The Springs at Tanasbourne for graciously donating space for our exercise class.

description.text:
In the exhibition Plurality of Expression, eight artists draw from realism, surrealism, and complete abstraction to present exciting worlds of color, emotion, and passion. We see photographs alongside paintings, each of which tell a compelling story, each with deep emotional impact. Whether featuring figures, still lifes, surreal patterns, or landscapes, the artists have captured a distinct message in their composition, one that tells the impact of human life, interactions, and natural elements. Not only are the works passionate and expressive, they are undoubtedly extraordinary feats in aesthetic and color.

description.text: The acclaimed workshop comes back to NYC!   "Menos es Más" (Spanish for "Less is More") is an Acting and Directing for the Camera workshop that consists of 2 student directors and 6 actors.  Together, actors and directors will shoot 3 scenes over the course of 5 days, with a professional Director of Photography. Scenes are then edited and screened for an in-depth critique by Juan Pablo Félix, the instructor. Woven into the practice are various discussions and lectures that invite the professional to further explore his/her technique. description.text:
Each program includes a community Meal for a time to grow together socially and foster friendships.  We will Pray and sing as we become comfortable worshiping together.  There will be a Video proclaiming the core Gospel messages and inviting us to respond personally to Jesus and finally, a Small Group Discussion about the video presentation with time for all to share insights. 
Most meetings are on Tuesday evenings.  We will meet on the following dates: 
January 19 January 26  February 2 February 9 February 12 (Saturday Retreat) February 16 February 21 (Sunday Closing Session) 
FAQs 
Is there any charge for these sessions? 
No.  Later sessions will provide an opportunity for a free will offering if you would like to make a donation. 
Is there child care available? 
Yes, if arranged in advance.  Please contact us at evangelization@stmoffice.com to make arrangements. 
What kind of meal will be served? 
The meal can be best described as a light supper.  There will be sandwiches or pasta/grains with a soup or salad and a dessert along with tea, coffee and soft drinks/water. Please let us know in advance if you have any food allergies or dietary restrictions. 
I may have to miss a session.  Can I still attend? 
Having a schedule conflict with a single session is not reason not to sign up for Discovering Christ.  However, if you know that you have conflicts with multiple sessions then it is probably best to wait until the course is offered again.   
What will the sessions be like? 
The evening will start with a meal with other members of your small group.  This will be a time to relax and get to know one another better.  Following the meal, there will be a brief intro to the session topic and some time for praise and worship.  Then we will watch the video on the evening's topic followed by a facilitated discussion within your small group.  We will end with closing comments by our leader. 
Who can I contact with any other questions? 
Please contact us at evangelization@stmoffice.com or call John or Mary Ann Hannigan at 248-258-0124.

description.text:
Join other Ridge Women as we study God's Word together at the Tuesday Evening Bible Study this year at the Bee Cave Campus!  
THE GOSPEL OF RUTH: Loving God Enough to Break the Rules, by Carolyn Custis James 
January 19 - April 12, 2016 | 6:30-8pm | $15 
This isn't the Ruth, the Naomi, or the Boaz we thought we knew. Carolyn Custis James has unearthed startling new insights from this well-worn story...insights that have life-changing implications for you. Naomi is no longer regarded as a bitter, complaining woman, but as a courageous overcomer. A female Job. Ruth, typically admired for her devotion to Naomi and her deference to Boaz, turns out to be a gutsy risk-taker and a powerful agent for change among God's people. She lives outside the box, and her love for Yahweh and Naomi compels her to break the rules of social and religious convention. The Gospel of Ruth vests every woman's life with kingdom purposes and frees us to embrace wholeheartedly God's calling, regardless of our circumstances or season of life. 
Come join us! 
Note: Childcare is not provided for evening Bible studies.

Do you want to grow your skills as a writer and increase your chances of getting published? Start the New Year off right with this 7-week virtual class—“Non-Fiction Writing: Getting Started” taught by author Mary J. Yerkes. A widely published author whose article, “Alone in Marriage,” was named one of the top 10 articles of 2015 on Christianity Today’s Gifted for Leadership online magazine, Mary combines years of real-world experience with helpful texts to give you the information and tools you need to take your writing to the next level. Learn how to write today’s most popular types of articles, refresh your knowledge of grammar and composition, strengthen your writing voice, and receive personalized edits and written critique of your work.
